  "rag_context": "The VHF Communication System operates on the VHF frequency band of 118-137 MHz, with a transmission power of 25W. It has a receiver sensitivity within 1dB accuracy and a communication latency below 50ms. The system design includes dual redundant circuitry for reliability and compliance with critical aviation standards such as DO-178/DO-254. The system is designed for short-range voice communication between aircraft and air traffic control, ensuring real-time communication, safety-critical redundancy, and seamless integration with the aircraft's communication network to support flight operations and operational safety.",
